name: Vessels 117: Story Beat 002
description:
3) A wide, establishing shot of a girl waking up in her bedroom. She stares straight up at the ceiling, a look of confusion on her face. The bedroom is very plain and functional; its occupant seems to have very few possessions. All we can really see are couple of framed photos and a rather worn and clearly homemade doll sitting on a shelf next to a few tattered books. Sunlight is shining in through the single small, dirty window.
BETSY (INTERNAL):  WHERE WAS I JUST THEN? IT’S ALREADY FADING… WAS THAT… A DREAM? OF COURSE IT WAS. IT JUST SEEMED SO VIVID. MAYBE…
